FBIS4-59072 "drnes091_j_94023" FBIS-NES-94-091 Daily Report 11 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Wrapup of Reports on Events in Yemen; Casualty Tolls Noted Wrapup of Reports on Events in Yemen; Casualty Tolls Noted North Yemen Offers `Immediate Cease-Fire' NC1105073194 Paris AFP in English 0724 GMT 11 May 94 NC1105073194 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Riyadh, May 11 (AFP) -- Northern Yemeni leaders offered an immediate ceasefire in the civil war on Wednesday if their southern rivals agreed to accept President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih's government, a Yemeni envoy said. Salih and his followers have ousted Vice-President 'Ali Salim al- Bid and other prominent southerners from the government since fighting broke out last week, accusing them of wanting secession. Planning Minister 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani, an envoy of Salih, said that the "political leadership in Sanaa is ready to accept an immediate ceasefire, on condition that they (the southerners) respect the constitution."
